(158, '<div class=\"title\"><strong> Prem Computer Institute</strong>\r\n<div class=\"title\">\r\n<h4>Profile of the Institute.</h4>\r\n<h4>About</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>As established by <strong>Budhrani Charitable Trust</strong> (Regd. Public Trust No. E9853 dated 17/1/84) on 14 March 2002 exclusively for the underprevileged members of Society, to provide computer training to socially downtrodden and economically weaker section of the society. <br>Budhrani Charitable Trust is eternally greatful to philanthropists, Mr. Gyanchandji Bothra and Parivar and Mr. Ramesh Thadani</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.omcomputers.in/images/img1.jpg\" width=\"604\" height=\"311\"></p>\r\n<h4>MS-CIT (Maharashtra State Certifcation in Information Technology)</h4>\r\n<p>Maharashtra Knowledge Corporation Limited (MKCL) has launched a state-wide IT Literacy drive in the form of Maharashtra State Certifcation in Information Technology Program (MS-CIT). The training given for this course is based on International Standards. It is compulsory for government jobs in Maharashtra.</p>\r\n<h3>Courses:</h3>\r\n<p>What you will learn :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Computer Fundamentals</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft Windows 7</li>\r\n<li>Microsoft Office 13</li>\r\n<li>Internet and Email</li>\r\n</ul>', 73),
