(217, 'veg thali', '150.00', '', 'Service', '<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h2>                          <span xss=removed>South Indian <strong>Thali</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p>                          <img src=\"https://s3.scoopwhoop.com/son/thali/south.jpg\" width=\"367\" height=\"226\"></p>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>We\'re sure you already know what it is, but for the uninitiated, the  humble Indian <em>Thali </em>is a composite and wholesome meal which is basically a combinations of various delicious dishes served on a single plate. You have small<em>katoris </em>(bowls) full of dishes like rice, <em>dal </em>, <em>sabzi </em>, curries and curd. You\'re also served different types of breads (rotis, naan, etc.) along with sides of <em>paapad </em>, pickle and salad!</span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>What\'s more, almost every Indian state and/or region has it\'s own distinctive version of the \"thali,\" made to suit local tastes and cooking styles. Here are a few that you should definitely try.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<h2>                               <span xss=removed>Bhojpuri Thali</span></h2>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>The Bhojpuri thali can surprise you with its multitude of flavours. The crispy bharbhara,</span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>the usual dahi chura for breakfast, golden brown sattu ka paratha, ghugni, the kala channa curry, besan ki sabji/  besan ki machhli and the sweet raw mango curries will take you on a culinary journey like no other.</span></p>\r\n<figure class=\"sw-media\">                            <img src=\"https://s3.scoopwhoop.com/son/thali/bhojpuri.jpg\" width=\"241\" height=\"308\"></figure>\r\n<h2>                         <span xss=removed>Maharashtrian Thali</span></h2>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>Maharashtrian cuisine is characterized by mildly spicy food. It usually features a few non-veg items and the dishes actually vary in different parts of Maharashtra. With sweets like aamras and sheera, the thali is certinaly not lacking when it comes to desserts.  Maharashtrian thali automatically goes up by a level. Then you have your sabudaana vada,  a refreshing glass of mattha, kanda poha, danyachi usal and the awesome pav bhaji, which rounds up this spectacular all-in-one meal.</span></p>\r\n<p>                              <img src=\"https://s3.scoopwhoop.com/son/thali/maharas.jpg\" width=\"283\" height=\"324\">  </p>\r\n<h2>                          <span xss=removed>Rajasthani Thali</span></h2>\r\n<p><span xss=removed>From gatte ki sabzi to daal-baati churma to khichda to laal maas to bajre ki roti to lahsun ki chutney... to... well, you get the point. The Rajasthani thali is the qunitessential Indian thali. You have stellar dishes like the mawa kachori from Jodhpur, juicy sweet rasgulle from Bikaner and malpuas from Pushkar. tasty treats from every nook and cranny of Rajasthan come together on plate for a food experience of a lifetime</span>.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"sw-media\">             <img src=\"https://s3.scoopwhoop.com/son/thali/rajasthani.JPG\" width=\"431\" height=\"324\"></figure>\r\n<p> </p>', 'Indians are known for elaborate meals and the South Indian thali is the best example of it. There is no \'rule\' to this thali and it contains liberal helpings of rice, sambhar, kootu ( vegetables curry cooked with lentils), kosumri, paapad, curd and for desert, there\'s akkaravadisal ( a sweet made with rice and lentils) to complete the meal.', 0, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med///', 1, 1, 1, 48, 0, 4, '2017-09-04 10:35:04', '2017-10-06 21:54:47'),
(218, 'Ayurvedic Herbs', '5000.00', 'item', 'Product', '<h1 class=\"entry-title title single-title\">Top 10 Ayurvedic Herbs:</h1>\r\n<h2>1. Turmeric</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/turmeric.jpg\" alt=\"turmeric\"></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-81\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/turmeric.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 340px) 100vw, 340px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/turmeric.jpg 340w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/turmeric-300x300.jpg 300w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/turmeric-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"turmeric\" width=\"340\" height=\"340\"></p>\r\n<p>Though commonly used as a spice for flavoring dishes, turmeric has great healing powers and has been used in Ayurveda for mostly for purifying blood, treating skin ailments, as well as in treatment of heart, liver and lungs diseases. Turmeric is considered great anti-bacterial, which helps in healing of wounds.</p>\r\n<h2>2. Garlic</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/garlic1.jpg\" alt=\"garlic\"></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-133 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/garlic1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 340px) 100vw, 340px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/garlic1.jpg 340w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/garlic1-300x200.jpg 300w\" alt=\"garlic\" width=\"340\" height=\"227\"></p>\r\n<p>This is one of the most sought after herb, both by the chefs and holistic medical practitioners, especially the Ayurvedic practitioners who refer to it as Lasuna. The herb is known for its excellent antiviral, antibacterial and antifungal property, besides being a good home remedy for influenza, cold and cough.</p>\r\n<h2>3. Aloe Vera</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/aloe-vera.jpg\" alt=\"aloe-vera\"></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-38\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/aloe-vera.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 337px) 100vw, 337px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/aloe-vera.jpg 337w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/aloe-vera-300x289.jpg 300w\" alt=\"aloe-vera\" width=\"337\" height=\"325\"></p>\r\n<p>The magical herb was known as ‘The Plant of Immortality’ by the Egyptians. <a href=\"http://www.medplants.net/herbs-used-in-cosmetics\">The herb is extensively used as cosmetic product</a> due to its qualities in nourishing the skin. In Ayurveda, the herb was used to treat rashes, digestion, and curing various ailments of human body.</p>\r\n<h2>4. Ginger</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-135 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/ginger1.jpg\" alt=\"ginger\" width=\"263\" height=\"179\"></p>\r\n<p>Ayurveda has taken advantage of this herb to successfully treat, digestive problems and morning sickness, though it is not limited to that. Ginger has been considered stand by remedy for almost any ailment due to its anti-inflammatory, anti-spasmodic, anti pyretic and analgesic properties.</p>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<h2>5. Tulsi or Holy Basil</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-75\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/tulsi-holy-basil.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 338px) 100vw, 338px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/tulsi-holy-basil.jpg 338w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/tulsi-holy-basil-300x205.jpg 300w\" alt=\"tulsi-holy-basil\" width=\"338\" height=\"232\"></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/tulsi-holy-basil.jpg\" alt=\"tulsi-holy-basil\"></p>\r\n<p>Holy basil or Tulsi is used as a remedial herb for many ailments of human body, like cold, fever, sore throat, cough, bronchitis, asthma, and kidney stones and heart problems. The herb is an excellent nerve tonic and is known to increase memory power and mental ability. It is also known to relieve stress.</p>\r\n<h2>6. Amla</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-137 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/amla.jpg\" alt=\"amla\" width=\"295\" height=\"190\"></p>\r\n<p>Amla, also known as Indian Gooseberry, has been an important ingredient of Ayurvedic medicine for many centuries. The edible fruit has been used to treat diabetes, cholesterol, cold, cough, indigestion and many more diseases effectively. Amla is well known for its high content in vitamin C and its amazing antioxidant properties.</p>\r\n<h2>7. Ashawagandh or Winter Cherry</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/ashwagandha-indian-ginseng.jpg\" alt=\"ashwagandha-indian-ginseng\"></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-86\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/ashwagandha-indian-ginseng.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 340px) 100vw, 340px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/ashwagandha-indian-ginseng.jpg 340w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/ashwagandha-indian-ginseng-300x218.jpg 300w\" alt=\"ashwagandha-indian-ginseng\" width=\"340\" height=\"248\"></p>\r\n<p>This herb has been used as an aphrodisiac and <a href=\"http://www.medplants.net/chinese-herbs-for-fertility\">treatment of infertility</a> as it has great property of nourishing and rejuvenating the tissues of human body. Ayurveda has found good use of the whole herb, from its root to its leaves for use in medicines which are used to address various ailments.</p>\r\n<h2>8. Jatamansi or Indian Spikenard</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-141 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/indian-spikenard.jpg\" alt=\"indian-spikenard\" width=\"300\" height=\"198\"></p>\r\n<p>This aromatic herb is sought for its amazing property of purifying blood and improving the complexion of skin, giving it a youthful appearance. The herb is used in ayurveda for treating ailments like poor circulation of blood, digestive disorders, respiratory diseases and infertility. It is also used in production of aromatic candles.</p>\r\n<h2>9. Neem</h2>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-52\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/neem-tree.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 340px) 100vw, 340px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/neem-tree.jpg 340w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/neem-tree-300x213.jpg 300w\" alt=\"neem-tree\" width=\"340\" height=\"242\"></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/neem-tree.jpg\" alt=\"neem-tree\"></p>\r\n<p>Neem is good for infections of skin, known to provide relief from even the dreaded small pox. Though bitter in taste, the plant has great healing power and used in most of medicines prepared in ayurveda.</p>\r\n<h2>10. Brahmi</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/brahmi-bacopa-monnieri.jpg\" alt=\"brahmi-bacopa-monnieri\"></p>\r\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-664\" src=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/brahmi-bacopa-monnieri.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 340px) 100vw, 340px\" srcset=\"http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/brahmi-bacopa-monnieri.jpg 340w, http://www.medplants.net/wp-content/uploads/brahmi-bacopa-monnieri-300x211.jpg 300w\" alt=\"brahmi-bacopa-monnieri\" width=\"340\" height=\"239\"></p>\r\n<p>Ayurveda has made use of this wonderful herb to enhance and rejuvenate memory powers as well as increase intelligence, as it greatly benefits the nervous system. The Brahmi or bacopa monnieri herb is also known to improve immunity. It treats psoriasis and hair loss as well.</p>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div class=\"post-single-content box mark-links entry-content\"> </div>\r\n<div class=\"single_post_right\"> </div>', 'Ayurveda is a medical science of ancient India, which had found a very effective use of herbs to cure all types of major and minor ailments, without any side effect. Though Ayurvedic doctors use rare and unique herbs in treating ailments, there are also some very popular herbs which can be used every day to maintain good health. You can consume most of these medicinal plants in the form of spices, condiments, and oils. So, make sure to use these herbs regularly, and you may never ever have to visit a doctor again.\r\n\r\n', 3, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med///', 1, 1, 1, 57, 0, 3, '2017-09-04 10:49:14', '2017-10-06 21:54:47'),
(219, 'Ayurvedic Medicines', '5000.00', 'item', 'Product', '<h2><strong>AYURVEDIC HERBAL MEDICINE:</strong></h2>\r\n<center><strong>\"Swasthasya Swasth Rakshnam, Aatursya Vikar Pra</strong><strong>shamnamch\"</strong></center><center></center><center></center><center></center><center></center><center><strong>1. JOINT AID PLUS</strong></center><center></center><center></center><center></center><center></center><center>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.shophealthy.in/image/cache/sellers/4390/Kishore-270x270.png\" alt=\"Image result for JOINT AID PLUS CAPSULES\"></p>\r\n<p><strong>Joint aid plus capsules contain pure and standardized extracts of Giloy (Tinospora cordifolia), Nirgundi (Vitex negundo), Ginger, Guggul (Commiphora mukul), Ashwagandha (Withania somniferum) and Shallaki (Boswellia serrata). All these herbs work together in a synergistic manner to impart anti – inflammatory action to the various joints that are attacked by the body\'s antibodies in patients of Rheumatoid arthritis. Rheumatoid arthritis is a hereditary disorder which cannot be completely cured, but with effective management of the symptoms, the progression of the disease can be easily controlled.</strong></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"h4\"><strong>2. BOSWELLIA CURCUMIN</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRGfcdJDMhqKafDfJu_qxR4GBIfOFPKqnueF2yFCSTmrHFjqjj8\" alt=\"Image result for boswellia curcumin\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Boswellia curcumin is a very effective herb that is well known in Ayurveda for its amazing effects on the joints and bones. Boswellia curcumin is a combination formulaton of two great anti-inflammatory herbs namely Boswellia serrata or Shallaki and Curcumin (active extracts of Turmeric). Both these herbs work wonderfully to protect the joints of Rheumatoid arthritis patients and help them to prevent further relapses and degradation.</strong></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"h4\"><strong>3. ASHWAGANDHA CAPSULES</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"http://www.organicveda.com/image/cache/data/catalog/organic-capsule-supplements/ashwagandha-root-capsules-245x348.jpg\" alt=\"Image result for ashwagandha capsules\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ashwagandha is a well-known rejuvenating herb and is useful for the patients of rheumatoid arthritis as it helps to maintain the balance of the all the three body doshas and is also a very effective immune – modulator. It prevents the joint degradation and deformities and also has anti – inflammatory action. It helps to maintain the lubrication in the joints and has a protective effect over them.</strong></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"h4\">4. AAMVATANTAKA CHURNA</h4>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://3.imimg.com/data3/IL/NP/MY-1440345/aamvatantak-churna-500x500.png\" alt=\"Image result for aam vatantak churna\" width=\"181\" height=\"373\"></p>\r\n<p><strong>Aamvatantaka churna is a combination of Ashwagandha (Withania somniferum), Fenugreek (Trigonella – foenum graecum), Suranjan (Colchicum luteum), Tinospora cordifolia, Gorakhmundi (Sphaerathus indicus) and sonth (Zingiber officianale). It is a natural detoxifying agent as it effectively removes all the toxins from the body that otherwise lead to Aamvata (Rheumatoid arthritis) according to Ayurveda.</strong></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"h4\"><strong>5. RUMOGIN  CAPSULES</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"http://5.imimg.com/data5/TI/IB/MY-441649/herbal-rheumatic-oil-500x500.jpg\" alt=\"Image result for rumawin capsules\" width=\"294\" height=\"294\"></strong></p>\r\n<h4 class=\"h4\"><strong>Rumogin capsules are a pure herbal formulation which comprise of </strong><strong>urcumin, Saunth, shallaki, Maricha and Pippali. This herbal combination works towards complete detoxification of the body as a result making the joints healthy and movable again. It aids in managing Rheumatoid arthritis effectively.</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong>DOSAGE</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT2wm9DQ1bMQBRWS1jSOVU8vbeYraSojom25R4zyf8IaO9Vs62cDYl0ug1L\" alt=\"Image result for dosage of ashwagandha\"></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Joint Aid Plus - 2 cap. Twice daily with plain water after meals.</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Boswellia Curcumin - 2 cap. Twice daily with plain water after meals.</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Ashwagandha Capsules - 2 capsule twice daily with plain water after meals.</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Aamvatantak Churna - 1 teaspoonful twice daily, 1 hr. after meals with plain water.</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>RumoGin 5 Capsules: 1 capsule twice daily with water after meal.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</center>\r\n<div class=\"spanX11\"> </div>\r\n<p> </p>', 'Ayurvedic treatment is a system of medicine that evolved in India and has survived as a distinct entity from ancient times to the present day. The true history of Ayurveda starts from the time of the ancient Holy books, the Vēdās. Scholars of the subject contend that the concept and essence of Ayurveda was revealed by the creator of the world Himself, Lord Brahma. References to medicine are found in the earliest texts including the Vedas. Agnivesa wrote the Samhita which is a classic and has survived to this day. It has been made available to the world by Charaka and is known as the Charaka Samhita.', 5, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med/1504785680_38.png', 1, 1, 1, 57, 0, 3, '2017-09-04 11:26:51', '2017-10-06 21:54:47'),
(220, 'chinese food', '150.00', '', 'Service', '<div id=\"contentHead\">\r\n<h1>chinese Food</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Chinese food is famous all over the world, but you may be shocked by its surprising range and variety of ingredients if you’ve only eaten in Chinese restaurants abroad. Chinese food has countless delicious and fantastic dishes. And people from different areas have different cuisine types, which can be bland, sweet, salty, spicy, or sour.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://assets.bwbx.io/images/users/iqjWHBFdfxIU/iP4CYmtFGAVU/v2/800x-1.jpg\" alt=\"Image result for chinese food\" width=\"298\" height=\"198\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"http://m.blog.hu/ko/konyhajatszoter/image/2012/china_food.jpg\" alt=\"Related image\" width=\"316\" height=\"421\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://data.chinahighlights.com/image/food/fried-rice.jpg\" alt=\"fried rice\" width=\"338\" height=\"165\">   </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://data.chinahighlights.com/image/food/sour-sweet-pork.jpg\" alt=\"sweet and sour pork\" width=\"357\" height=\"174\"> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://data.chinahighlights.com/image/food/eastern-food.jpg\" alt=\"tea and snacks\" width=\"361\" height=\"176\"></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"https://tse4.mm.bing.net/th?id=OIP.JmrA6N8dIqofSvsQGe7i3QEsC7&pid=15.1&P=0&w=294&h=184\" width=\"374\" height=\"234\"></strong></p>\r\n<p> </p>', 'Chinese Food\r\nChinese food is famous all over the world, but you may be shocked by its surprising range and variety of ingredients if you’ve only eaten in Chinese restaurants abroad. Chinese food has countless delicious and fantastic dishes. And people from different areas have different cuisine types, which can be bland, sweet, salty, spicy, or sour.', 0, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med///', 1, 1, 1, 123, 0, 4, '2017-09-06 04:46:44', '2017-10-06 21:54:47'),
(221, 'batball', '500.00', 'item', 'Product', '<p><span xss=removed><strong><em>A cricket bat is a specialised piece of equipment used by <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Batsmen\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batsmen\">batsmen</a> in the sport of <a title=\"Cricket\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket\">cricket</a> to hit the <a title=\"Cricket ball\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_ball\">ball</a>, typically consisting of a cane handle attached to a flat-fronted <a title=\"Willow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willow\">willow</a>-wood blade. The length of the bat may be no more than 38 inches (965 mm) and the width no more than 4.25 inches (108 mm). Its use is first mentioned in 1624. Since 1979, the <a title=\"Dennis Lillee\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dennis_Lillee#Aluminium_bat_incident\">rule change</a> stipulated that bats can only be made from wood.</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span xss=removed><em> </em></span></strong></p>\r\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"> </div>', 'A cricket bat is a specialised piece of equipment used by batsmen in the sport of cricket to hit the ball, typically consisting of a cane handle attached to a flat-fronted willow-wood blade. The length of the bat may be no more than 38 inches (965 mm) and the width no more than 4.25 inches (108 mm). Its use is first mentioned in 1624. Since 1979, the rule change stipulated that bats can only be made from wood.\r\n\r\n', 0, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med///', 1, 2, 0, 49, 0, 6, '2017-09-06 05:24:31', '2017-10-06 21:54:47'),
