5b6a728094edc 930w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"465px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380124880896/Sailing-Catamaran-off-the-010.jpg?w=465&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=55fa80bc4b5cde9da6cb9581c0e80b94 465w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"465px\"><img class=\"maxed responsive-img\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380124880896/Sailing-Catamaran-off-the-010.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=75e31341a1c4e4ccece540733df94cda\" alt=\"Sailing Catamaran off the Tobago Coast\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--main caption--img\"> The Buccoo-reef protected area of Tobago\'s Pigeon Point and the sheltered Bon Accord lagoon next to it are good sailing spots for all levels. Photograph: Ralph A Clevenger</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<div class=\"content__meta-container js-content-meta js-football-meta u-cf\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \">\r\n<div class=\"meta__extras  meta__extras--notice \">\r\n<div class=\"meta__social\" data-component=\"share\">\r\n<ul class=\"social social--top js-social--top u-unstyled u-cf\" data-component=\"social\">\r\n<li class=\"social__item social__item--facebook \" data-link-name=\"facebook\"></li>\r\n<li class=\"social__item social__item--twitter \" data-link-name=\"twitter\"></li>\r\n<li class=\"social__item social__item--email \" data-link-name=\"email\"></li>\r\n<li class=\"js-social__secondary social__item social__item--more js-social__item--more\">&lt;button class=\"meta-button social-tray__button\"&gt;<span class=\"u-h\">View more sharing options</span>&lt;/button&gt;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"meta__numbers\">\r\n<div class=\"meta__number js-sharecount\" title=\"Facebook: 571\">\r\n<h3 class=\"sharecount__heading\"><span class=\"sharecount__text u-h\">Shares</span></h3>\r\n<div class=\"sharecount__value sharecount__value--full\">571</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"meta__number\" data-commentcount-format=\"content\" data-discussion-closed=\"false\">\r\n<h3 class=\"commentcount2__heading\"><span class=\"commentcount2__text u-h\">Comments</span></h3>\r\n<a class=\"commentcount2 tone-colour\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2013/oct/01/top-10-water-sports-activities-tobago#comments\" data-link-name=\"Comment count\"><span class=\"commentcount2__value tone-colour js_commentcount_actualvalue\">0</span></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"byline\" data-link-name=\"byline\" data-component=\"meta-byline\">Dylan Kerrigan</p>\r\n<p class=\"content__dateline\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><time class=\"content__dateline-wpd js-wpd\" datetime=\"2013-10-01T06:00:00+0100\" data-timestamp=\"1380603600000\">Tuesday 1 October 2013 <span class=\"content__dateline-time\">06.00 BST</span></time></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content__article-body from-content-api js-article__body\" data-test-id=\"article-review-body\">\r\n<h2>Sailing</h2>\r\n<p>Sailing around Tobago can be both idyllic and tough depending, on the wind conditions and coastline. While the north of the island has many protected bays for anchorage, the choppy windward side is only for experts. The best sailing conditions are to be found from December to May, when winds are strong and consistent. The Buccoo-reef protected area of Pigeon Point and the sheltered Bon Accord lagoon next to it are good sailing spots for all levels, particularly those with little experience – 13ft Hobie Waves are available to rent there and are ideal for beginners.</p>\r\n<p>Another way to travel wind-assisted around the island is on a catamaran charter. With food, drinks and music provided, plus stops at a few tropical bays, the trips are more \"party on a catamaran\" than real sailing. <br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Radical Sports, +1868 631 5150, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.radicalsportstobago.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">radicalsportstobago.com</a>; Catamaran Charters +1868 639 7245, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.sailtobago.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">sailtobago.com</a></em></p>\r\n<h2>Kitesurfing</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654350\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=7058f6abd00812780d57497a4103533f 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=c058aa6eeac79cd059503307afff0e0a 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=bc26d3e46ff0c67c51f136e8587c8a81 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=a79f93a09fdedec845d297fe68e448ad 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=0e07aebe50acb174f63b28dbde40bd3f 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=84f3b15889dc89aba2761bd36bcffb6a 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/26/1380208511019/Kitesurfing.-010.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=c0525022a89f2b4838dc003571d0d532\" alt=\"Kitesurfing.\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Tobago\'s south-western Pigeon Point peninsula is a particularly blustery piece of coastline, ideal for water sports requiring wind. It also has clear, shallow waters encircled by the Buccoo Reef, and is popular with kitesurfers of all abilities. With friendly, safety-conscious instructors and equipment available on the peninsula, you can take it at your own speed and wait for winds that suit you. <br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Tobago Kiteboarding Organization, +1868 331 3775, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.tobagokiteboardingorganization.webs.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">tobagokiteboardingorganization.webs.com</a></em></p>\r\n<h2>Scuba diving</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654351\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=4bc72bd7b691f6ba74a4044c4fb16b5d 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=952feeb55e69ee6a1852c798e2dafe7e 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=95e1891620efe66222b9dc4f59ec61a7 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=e2724ad08e8c484f4552f706d634b049 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=51692ee3bc7a26150d8980de4e6a0e3b 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=2fcf48809e8798a28927f33623570f81 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125438900/Scub-diver-Tobago-001.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=d73067d1aa46c81497d878923276ea98\" alt=\"Scub diver, Tobago\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Tobago is a well-known dive destination: with more than 60 established dive sites, some say it is the best in the Caribbean. Tobago\'s waters cater for all levels of experience, offering shallow-reef dives for beginners, as well as more technical dives, such as drift, wreck and deep diving. The north side of the island, particularly around Speyside and Charlotteville, contains Tobago\'s most famous dive sites, as well as the island\'s only recompression chamber. Dive sites in the southern part of the island are also plentiful, but visibility is not always as good. Dive shops are located all over the island; the most safety conscious ones are members of the Association of Tobago Dive Operators (ATDO).<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>AquaMarine Dive, +1868 639 4416, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.aquamarinedive.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">aquamarinedive.com</a></em></p>\r\n<h2>Snorkelling</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654352\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=6dc2821f02ed6a68a09e782698f0bf3a 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=2f447e2dde6b47bc49288c6f683e4e7e 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=d631de403a4d60a534354fa1e2a7c739 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=e2341882761351c4024ad264d9b49655 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=11430815d60cc133ff5828d6023f0250 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=7b2214da076cd77f64ec34c146f912a9 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/24/1380019545814/BA-Islands-snorkelling-wi-010.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=0f4ac836ba46631f6a867e7142a16c22\" alt=\"BA Islands: snorkelling with green turtle\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>You don\'t need to take a boat ride to find great snorkelling spots; there are many at the end of several popular beaches. However, Buccoo Reef – a complex ecosystem composed of 30 acres of coral reef that are perfect for peering into – is most easily reached by glass-bottom boat tours from Store Bay (or Pigeon Point). Glass-bottom boat operators provide snorkels and tickets are available on a walk-up basis.<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Diving in Tobago, +1868 639 7936, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.divingintobago.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">divingintobago.com</a></em></p>\r\n<h2>Windsurfing</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654353\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=ef92652ef9b146aa821bf35303686f49 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=4b01cadefb5c9ef5889899f87877e97a 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=a950ca7c76c83433937a2b2cfc0b390e 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=32321e6dbb6f320cebe8bf57ca2f433e 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=cb68f01d0ae1590b9510da2e6bcb9fd3 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=0579975d2184aac7c77a011ee1944a75 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380125930287/Windsurfing-Pigeon-Point--008.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=f0e8d46cedbb7ca70f52ba55428303d3\" alt=\"Windsurfing, Pigeon Point Tobago\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>The centre for windsurfing on the island is, again, Pigeon Point peninsula. Winds are best between December and June, and it is common to see windsurfers speeding far into the distance. This period is also best for windsurfing clinics, run by local operators and international companies who specialise in windsurfing holidays. During the rest of the year, the conditions are great for beginners.<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Radical Sports, as above</em></p>\r\n<h2>Parasailing</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654354\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=400a7c7c7714c92ac4c4edd1dfbe5559 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=7f4747377038fcde0569ef69e7db0b50 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=d52da8b59a2e57ccaed72446d4df1ee3 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=3293b4a0c3688addf64ac7bb221d320b 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=37d781f2ffc3078b10928e4d56c06747 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=4e94a0362275a4ec26832e029df9bc45 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126183616/Parasailing---008.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=8b551713b77a59b2d9382d27b7bd5ff1\" alt=\"Parasailing  \"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>One of the worst things you can do in the tropics is to get drunk in the hot sun and not hydrate properly. The doctors call it sunstroke; unsympathetic friends and family call it a really bad hangover. Strapped into a parachute, winched up into the air and floating 90 metres above Buccoo reef isn\'t the most obvious way to overcome such a condition – but, surprisingly, it worked for me, thanks to the panoramic vistas, cool breeze and sheer effortlessness. Parasailing is great for all ages and abilities. Slow or twin glides are available, and, in most cases, your feet will never touch the water.<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Tobago Kite and Surf Camp, +1868 313 1260, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.surfcamp-tobago.com/en/parasailing\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">surfcamp-tobago.com/en/parasailing</a></em></p>\r\n<h2>Sea kayaking</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654355\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=660e6e7a4165d0f158beedf8eed7dda4 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=f9490d4993867b7f7fd37e498dbfe1ae 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=e9eb728bfe328a54adb93a1706183046 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=83fe7f4bc1427f67e5fc01408934cbf2 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=c6cf652157a1dfbe0f568fdbfbb2e375 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=b5aa37adac36b0de031a56889c906af4 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126314019/Sea-kayaking-Tobago-001.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=5e762d8d9fddffaf90150d6e121431ab\" alt=\"Sea kayaking, Tobago\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Fred Hoogervorst</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>One of the calmest and most scenic water sports in Tobago is sea kayaking. It\'s great for all the family and many of the beach hotels have kayaks available for their guests. A variety of sea kayaks – sit-on-top, recreational and touring ¬– can also be rented from water-sport providers. Kayaking around the Bon Accord lagoons and mangroves is a good way to see wildlife. Another popular kayaking spot is Charlotteville (11.31806, -60.54986), with its coves that can only be reached by sea. Kayak tours of other parts of the island, plus lessons, can be easily organised.<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Tobago Sea Kayak Experience, Charlotteville, +1868 660 6186</em></p>\r\n<h2>Surfing</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654356\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=bf2dc2e136b1771cb8ebf2d912b935c4 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=95a1533dee5f05f0cb31d62f625edb45 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=09d652d2d11662cdc84577af0e1d54e8 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=6a96bea0b47419d8db597d54537118ba 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=e5b3c34314a47581707f2edd5b615f39 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=01451b95aba8755f0cbd8faa5c07694e 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126420571/Surfing-in-Tobago--001.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=c7503333860d6bdc51669b2408b4af9a\" alt=\"Surfing in Tobago \"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Mount Irvine is the number one surf spot in Tobago. While the size of the waves depends on the direction of the swells and the time of year, when it\'s big at Mount Irvine it\'s massive – three to four metres in the back and six to seven metres in the face. With a shallow, coral bottom, when this break is pounding it isn\'t for the faint-hearted. On the other side of the bay, \"Lefts\" is another popular spot and, with its sandy bottom, is a lot less gnarly. However, big swells are not regular and, more often than not, the waves at Mount Irvine are waist-high. They have a perfect shape and, with a good local instructor, Mount Irvine is great place to learn to surf, with schools located on the beach. Other popular waves in Tobago include the choppy \"Crazies\", off Bacolet Point, and the outer reef at Pigeon Point. These waves are more suited to advanced surfers, however<br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>High Tide Surf Lessons, Mount Irvine, +1868 294 6509</em></p>\r\n<h2>Wakeboarding</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654357\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=81937f4934e475599e5fcdf766a78da1 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=9d0d03ec3673debac6279ed9f315be71 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=d4b6ef414bd59ea11f00cbfb68709cba 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=a0233415f0fa1cad008acc7e7cac8d8a 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=41835b10611a85e2997e0231b57c8429 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=81c2003184eb07751ce45e4ef6eda87f 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126767760/Wake-boarder-in-Tobago.-001.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=d8a13f5e939d287cb828c44282836bc3\" alt=\"Wake boarder in Tobago.\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Wakeboarding is to waterskiing what snowboarding is to skiing: you\'re strapped to a single board rather than two skies. Radical Sports Tobago, the biggest water-sports centre on the island, offers lessons and all the equipment you need to get standing in no time. They also welcome those with prior experience, who they are then quick to encourage into wake jumps, 180s and more. <br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Radical Sports Tobago, as above</em></p>\r\n<h2>Stand up paddling</h2>\r\n<figure class=\"element element-image img--landscape  \" data-component=\"image\" data-media-id=\"gu-image-418654358\">\r\n<div class=\"u-responsive-ratio\"><picture><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=620&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=c7ff27de7da2416f9078c3b09669b0c9 1240w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 660px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=620&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=a2006bc363905d53a060c0dddfaebfa1 620w\" media=\"(min-width: 660px)\" sizes=\"620px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=605&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=e7ff960423e8968e4d1d083f916db0a6 1210w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=605&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=4b54c49ee47f4b69f4ab09d155a0a3c2 605w\" media=\"(min-width: 480px)\" sizes=\"605px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=445&q=20&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&dpr=2&s=4a0c5e18800a895d4deee7f71d0d3ecb 890w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 0px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)\" sizes=\"445px\"><source srcset=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=445&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=023ccb030f6184255d15099391438578 445w\" media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" sizes=\"445px\"><img class=\"gu-image\" src=\"https://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Travel/Pix/pictures/2013/9/25/1380126960492/Stand-Up-Paddling.-001.jpg?w=300&q=55&auto=format&usm=12&fit=max&s=84fa32b51ccb3f3668bf4b3e5d2d251a\" alt=\"Stand Up Paddling.\"></picture></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption caption--img caption caption--img\"> Photograph: Alamy</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p>Stand up paddling (SUP) is one of the more recent additions to the Tobago water-sport scene. It looks very Hawaii Five-0 when done by experts: for novices, sedate paddle cruises around the calm waters of Petit Trou lagoon are a good way to start. There are other options too, including stand-up fitness and yoga paddling. <br><span class=\"bullet\">•</span> <em>Stand Up Paddle Tobago +1868 681 4741, <a class=\"u-underline\" href=\"http://www.standuppaddletobago.com/\" data-link-name=\"in body link\">standuppaddletobago.com</a></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Dylan Kerrigan is an anthropologist at The University of the West Indies, writes regularly for the Trinidad Guardian and he lives in Port of Spain</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"contributions__epic \" data-component=\"mem_acquisition_epic_kr1_epic_ask_four_earning_control\">\r\n<div class=\"\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h2 class=\"contributions__title contributions__title--epic\">Since you’re here …</h2>\r\n<p class=\"contributions__paragraph contributions__paragraph--epic\">… we have a small favour to ask. More people are reading the Guardian than ever but advertising revenues across the media are falling fast. And <span class=\"contributions__highlight\">unlike many news organisations, we haven’t put up a paywall – we want to keep our journalism as open </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"contributions__paragraph contributions__paragraph--epic\"> <span class=\"contributions__highlight\">unlike many news organisations, we haven’t put up a paywall – we want to keep our journalism as open as we can</span>. So you can see why we need to ask for your help. The Guardian’s independent, investigative journalism takes a lot of time, money and hard work to produce. But we do it because we believe our perspective matters – because it might well be your perspective, too.</p>\r\n<div class=\"epic__testimonial-container epic__testimonial-container--subtle\">\r\n<div class=\"epic__testimonial-quote epic__testimonial-quote--subtle\"> </div>\r\n<blockquote class=\"epic__testimonial-text\">I appreciate there not being a paywall: it is more democratic for the media to be available for all and not a commodity to be purchased by a few. I’m happy to make a contribution so others with less means still have access to information.<cite class=\"epic__testimonial-name\">Thomasine F-R.</cite></blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"contributions__paragraph contributions__paragraph--epic\">If everyone who reads our reporting, who likes it, helps to support it, our future would be much more secure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"contributions__paragraph contributions__paragraph--epic\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRMs7r4avV7oXIztiN1dWLnT9mNrGNWK7BddHwi9O6uAGz4vwEc4g\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ-wPkDF4KhE1XSZe0E66Smp8XXNhZcLlbbJqq5DO___Qp3dPQF\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQH5PAklQQK7pLK4c1Qmqh6tV2MCUs49cqHG7XaLfaaKom94du3Hg\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"contributions__paragraph contributions__paragraph--epic\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQaaMXQj_d9Bt8KaNVUD9bzVCId4XfSSClxWMoYL2-yj-kMLaPV\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSr9PPyngNC0Kbmp6a152wPh-Xc8yoHl5YK66PVBGHGDxoQ4l0j\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTGbRUzhQID5gOHSshadGl99ZqE7Ij2PJXHynQ2PNzAlSyWwELh\" alt=\"water sport साठी प्रतिमा परिणाम\"></p>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__heading\">\r\n<h2 class=\"b-title \">Shop by Category</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__grid\">\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/rbcAAOSwiQ9ZSFdr/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Kayaks\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Kayaks</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/RI8AAOSw0j9ZSFeY/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Canoes\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Canoes</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/ti8AAOSw-89ZSFe8/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Stand Up Paddleboards\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Stand Up Paddleboards</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/NrYAAOSwpONZSFff/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Surfboards\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Surfboards</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/uTMAAOSw-89ZSFgF/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Kitesurfing\" width=\"225\" height=\"193\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Kitesurfing</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/kusAAOSw3h1ZSFgw/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"SCUBA & Snorkeling\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">SCUBA & Snorkeling</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/SVgAAOSwAO9ZSFkn/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Wakeboarding & Waterskiing\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Wakeboarding & Waterskiing</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/twcAAOSwRXRZSFlU/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Life Jackets & Preservers\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Life Jackets & Preservers</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/Oc4AAOSwvflZSFl7/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Wetsuits\" width=\"103\" height=\"225\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Wetsuits</div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__img\"><img class=\"b-img\" role=\"\" src=\"https://i.ebayimg.com/thumbs/images/g/w6wAAOSwiQ9ZSFms/s-l225.webp\" alt=\"Swimming Equipment\" width=\"225\" height=\"67\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"b-visualnav__title\">Swimming Equipment</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Browse Watersports Gear on eBay\r\n\r\nWhether you’re a watersports junkie or just dipping your toe in the shallow end, eBay has all of your watersports equipment needs covered. From swimwear and caps to windsurf boards and kayak paddles, our comprehensive watersports store will let you enjoy all your favorite activities in the pool or open water.\r\n\r\nSwimming Pool Supplies\r\n\r\nIf you’re swimming laps or splashing around with little ones, you’ll want to browse our broad selection of swim necessities, including swimming goggles from favorite brands like Aqua Sphere and Arena’s swimwear and safety collection. For accessories like kickboards and waterproof lap counters, check out eBay’s vast array of swimming training aids.', 0, 0, 0.00, '//www.bigmee.com/dist/img/products/med///', 1, 1, 1, 110, 0, 6, '2017-09-14 07:02:47', '2017-10-06 21:54:47');
